If you are looking for an innovative startup-style company with a good team spirit that has the support of an internationally recognized brand, we encourage you to apply and join us!
WHO WE ARE
With offices in 20 countries and more than 25 years of experience in North America, Keyrus is a trusted leader in Data Intelligence.
Keyrus Canada offers stimulating projects to increase companies’ performance, with 2 areas of expertise:
Data Strategy
to help organizations identify business objectives, build a strategy, and leverage their data to achieve their goals (BI Roadmap | Master Data Management | Data Governance and Architecture…)
Data Intelligence
to enable companies to draw critical insights from their data and shape business decisions (Data Integration | Cloud Migration | Business Intelligence | Analytics & Machine Learning…)
ABOUT THE ROLE
Your responsibilities will include :
Conducting impact studies and providing estimates;
Documenting Business Intelligence and Information Management solutions;
Supporting applications in production and providing support to your colleagues throughout the production process;
Designing and developing reports and dashboards for informational/operational needs according to best practices;
Performing and documenting tests (unit/integrated) for the solutions in which you participated;
Carrying out these activities while respecting and promoting the Business Intelligence norms and standards established by the organization;
Coaching your team members and colleagues;
Conducting multi-disciplinary and multi-level stakeholder meetings and synthesizing in non-technical language;
Writing documents and making presentations for an internal community of users.
Our ideal candidate :
3-years professional college diploma, or the academic equivalent in a relevant field
Experience as an analyst in a Business Intelligence context (business needs, data analysis, functional specifications, multidimensional modeling, etc.)
Knowledge of the field and Business Intelligence environments (ETL tools, data profiling tools, data access tools, data model, ORACLE RDBMS, DB2, etc.), an asset
2 - 3 years of experience with Tableau
Tool certification an asset
Knowledge of Data Visualization and "DataStory Telling" best practices
Excellent level in French and English
What we offer
A stimulating environment where you will be able to surpass yourself and discover new horizons;
A strong culture of innovation and entrepreneurship;
Many occasions to celebrate your success : 5 @ 7, team activities, birthdays, breakfasts and other special events;
Group insurance for you and your family members;
RRSP and DPSP participation plan;
Reimbursement of immigration fees;
Reimbursement of transport costs;
Reimbursement of telecommunication costs;
Referral program;
Flexible work from home policy;
4 weeks of paid vacation;
Language courses (French & English);
Access to continuing education (in-house, conferences, events, courses, certifications, etc.);
Development plan for each employee and coaching.

Senior Systems Biologist / Senior Computational Biologist
My Intelligent Machines (MIMs) is looking for a talented Senior Systems Biologist / Senior Computational Biologist to join a dynamic team building a world class augmented intelligence R&D platform for life scientists working in BioPharma and agriculture companies.
MIMs is a fast-growing software company, with a dynamic and gender balanced team building a world class augmented intelligence platform for R&D life scientists working in BioPharma and agriculture companies, helping them to stratify patient populations, to identify drug targets and biomarkers and to develop more efficient and personalized treatments and Agro-Products.
Reporting directly to the lead of MIMs solutions team, you will work closely with life scientists, bioinformaticians, biostatisticians, data scientists, AI and software engineers. This full time position will focus on designing data integration and multi-omic modelling strategies and to support their implementations within MIMs solutions. Ideal candidates will have a strong background in systems biology, statistical modelling, machine learning, and data analysis, particularly as applied to large-scale, high-dimensional data sets. In particular, we are interested in candidates who have experience with multi-omic data modalities to support the inference of gene functionality and co-functionality, functional interaction, systems modelling applied to systems stratification, biomarkers and drug targets identification.
Main Responsibilities
Provide scientific leadership in the goals, architecture, and implementation of multi-omic data integration and modelling aspects of solutions developed at MIMs;
Work with scientists and software developers of the solution team to identify, adapt or develop pipelines and methods;
Lead the biological validation of developed solutions;
Work with data scientists to define appropriate data structure and ontology to be used by the solutions;
Collaborate with UX-designer and front-end developers to ensure optimal user-flow, human/machine synergy and facilitate results interpretation;
Contribute to manuscripts and software documentation resulting from standards development or scientific results.
Qualifications
Expert in the computational and mathematical analysis and modeling of complex biological systems;
A Ph.D. in computational biology, bioinformatics, biomedical engineering or related quantitative discipline and 3+ years of postdoc or post-graduate experience in systems biology;
Ideal candidates will have a strong background in systems biology, statistical modeling, machine learning, and data analysis, particularly as applied to large-scale, high-dimensional multi-omic data sets;
Proficient in applying graph theories to biology / network biology;
Programing skills in Python;
Excellent verbal and written communication skills (English/French);
Experience with writing unit-tests/performing code review is a plus.
Who you are
The ideal candidate is exceptionally detail-oriented and derives joy from bringing rigor, structure, and organization to large datasets, complex systems, and intricate analyses;
You have a proven track record of analyzing/interpreting complex interactions within biological systems;
You derive satisfaction from thoroughly and thoughtfully describing a system for both technical and non-technical audiences;
Superlative organizational, interpersonal, and communication skills;
A flexible attitude to job roles as well as a willingness to contribute wherever needed:he ideal candidate will take full ownership of their core responsibilities, and will be comfortable with those responsibilities evolving with the changing needs of the company;
Ability to contribute in a multidisciplinary team as a strong team player, focused on delivering results against multiple deadlines in a fast-paced growing environment.
Submission
Please submit your resume or any questions you may have to
hr@mims.ai
. We thank all those who apply but only those selected for further consideration will be contacted.
About MIMs
My Intelligent Machines (MIMs), based in Montreal, is a leader in artificial intelligence applied to life sciences. We provide Biopharma and Agtech companies with augmented intelligence systems enabling life scientists working in this space to model patients, cells, tissues or farm animals to develop more efficient and personalized treatments and agro-products. The company is growing at a fast pace and has a strong and active research and development team.
MIMs is a dynamic tech company with an exceptional culture which embraces diversity and gender equity. We are currently one of the few tech companies reaching gender balance, as half of the team is composed of women. We received the 2020 Red Herring’s Top 100 North America Award, one of the most prestigious prizes granted each year to the 100 most promising private tech companies.
